@paragraph: That explains a lot.

<cite>But not really an everyday object?</cite>

Depends on age. When I was twelve a basketball was an everyday object.

- Ice-cold drinks. Everything ‘on the rocks’. _Even vodka_;
- Automatic transmission;
- Disdain for diacritics—to the point when using them looks pretentious (e.g., _résumé_).
